one of every 10,000 people suffer from the disease.

14
00:00:40,649 --> 00:00:43,079
The next day, the doctor calls with terrible news.

15
00:00:43,079 --> 00:00:47,179
She says that we have tested positive for the disease. So now we're panicking.

16
00:00:47,179 --> 00:00:50,519
But before panicking, let's turn to math and actually

17
00:00:50,520 --> 00:00:54,390
calculate what is the probability of being sick. So, here's a quiz.

18
00:00:54,390 --> 00:00:57,649
Given the two pieces of information that the test has

19
00:00:57,649 --> 00:01:02,740
99 percent accuracy and that one out of every 10,000 people have the disease,

20
00:01:02,740 --> 00:01:06,284
what do you think the probability is that we're sick?

21
00:01:06,284 --> 00:01:09,994
Is it from zero to 20 percent, from 20 to 40,

22
00:01:09,995 --> 00:01:12,675
40 to 60, 60 to 80,

23
00:01:12,674 --> 00:01:14,759
